WEBVTT

00:01.918 --> 00:03.753
{\an5}WOW!

00:01.918 --> 00:03.753
Girl: ♪ I GOT THE BEAT ♪

00:04.129 --> 00:06.464
♪ SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE
WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:06.715 --> 00:08.758
♪ PICK IT UP, TURN AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:09.008 --> 00:11.302
[♪...]

00:13.263 --> 00:14.764
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, HEY) ♪

00:14.848 --> 00:16.850
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, LA) ♪

00:17.100 --> 00:19.394
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:19.644 --> 00:21.646
♪ I GOT THE BEAT SO ALL THE KIDS
DANCE WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:22.063 --> 00:25.942
♪ STICK 'EM UP, ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:26.025 --> 00:29.696
[♪...]

00:29.946 --> 00:31.948
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:32.031 --> 00:33.575
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B. ♪

00:33.825 --> 00:35.618
[MUSIC ENDS]

00:37.245 --> 00:40.498
Captioning Provided By:
MTV NETWORKS

00:40.749 --> 00:42.167
[♪...]

00:47.756 --> 00:50.508
Bessie: HAPPY, HAPPY, HAPPY,
HAPPY, IT'S STARTING.

00:50.759 --> 00:52.427
TV Announcer: When threatened,
the sea cucumber will engage

00:52.677 --> 00:54.888
{\an5}in defensive vomiting...

00:52.677 --> 00:54.888
Bessie: OOH...

00:55.263 --> 00:57.265
...barfing out their intestines
to scare off predators.

00:57.515 --> 00:59.434
{\an5}A sea cucumber can
regenerate its organs

00:57.515 --> 00:59.434
[SNORING]

00:59.768 --> 01:01.728
within just one month.

01:01.978 --> 01:04.813
{\an1}HAPPY, HAPPY,
YOU'RE MISSING IT.

01:04.897 --> 01:06.232
[IRRITATED GRUMBLE]

01:06.483 --> 01:08.151
[GASPS] JUST A REPEAT?

01:08.401 --> 01:10.528
YOU LOVE "SEA CUCUMBER COLONY."

01:10.779 --> 01:12.238
[YAWNING]

01:15.074 --> 01:16.993
[HAPPY SNORES]

01:17.285 --> 01:19.996
Bessie: OH, HI DONALD.

01:20.079 --> 01:21.998
CAN I GIVE YOU
A HAND WITH THE MAIL?

01:22.081 --> 01:23.166
Donald: OH, BESSIE,
THAT'S SO NICE OF...

01:23.416 --> 01:25.335
JUST KIDDING.

01:25.585 --> 01:27.670
{\an3}TAMPERING WITH THE MAIL
IS A FEDERAL OFFENSE.

01:27.921 --> 01:30.006
{\an3}[CHUCKLES]: OK, I'M NOT GONNA
WRITE YOU UP THIS TIME.

01:30.089 --> 01:31.841
{\an4}Donald:
WHA... HEY?

01:30.089 --> 01:31.841
{\an3}OK, SEE YOU
LATER, DONALD.

01:32.217 --> 01:33.259
OH, MAN, THAT GETS HIM
EVERY TIME, HUH, HAP...

01:36.846 --> 01:37.388
[SNORING...]

01:42.101 --> 01:43.061
Bessie: DINNER, BOY,
COME AND GET IT.

01:48.441 --> 01:50.902
[YAWNS]

01:50.985 --> 01:54.739
OOH, WHAT IS THE CHEF SELECTION
TODAY, YOU ASK?

01:54.989 --> 01:56.741
"DUMPSTER DELIGHT."

01:56.991 --> 01:58.535
YOUR ALL-TIME FAVORITE, HAPPY.

01:58.785 --> 02:00.578
LET'S SEE, HM...

02:00.829 --> 02:03.039
IT'S PACKED WITH DOGGIE
DELICACIES LIKE

02:03.122 --> 02:05.041
STALE BREAD...

02:05.124 --> 02:07.919
GOBLIN DANDER AND,
OOH, WHAT'S THIS?

02:08.002 --> 02:08.127
FISH CHUNKS.

02:12.006 --> 02:13.883
[SIGHS]

02:13.967 --> 02:14.926
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT SICK, BOY.

02:15.176 --> 02:15.343
[SNORING]

02:20.515 --> 02:22.350
WHAT... WHAT FINGER?

02:22.600 --> 02:24.018
WELL, THAT'S NONE OF
MY BUSINESS, BUT...

02:24.102 --> 02:25.937
WHAT, WHERE?

02:26.020 --> 02:27.939
FINGER, YOU SHOULDN'T
BE DOING THIS.

02:28.022 --> 02:29.732
YOU SHOULDN'T BE
OPENING UP THIS BAG.

02:29.983 --> 02:31.025
THIS IS NOT YOUR
BUSINESS, HMM...

02:31.109 --> 02:31.734
WHAT'S THIS?

02:34.404 --> 02:36.447
[GROWLING SNARL]

02:36.698 --> 02:38.157
{\an3}WELL, I DIDN'T REALIZE I WAS
INTRUDING ON YOUR PRIVACY.

02:44.163 --> 02:46.291
ASTRONAUT...
I'M AN ASTRONAUT.

02:46.541 --> 02:48.084
LANDED ON THE SUN.

02:48.334 --> 02:51.045
I NEED... WATER.

02:51.129 --> 02:52.922
I NEED TO GET SOME WATER.

02:53.214 --> 02:55.633
IT'S VERY HARD TO BE AN
ASTRONAUT ON THE SUN.

02:55.884 --> 02:58.219
YES, SIR,
I'M GONNA SAVE OUR COUNTRY.

02:58.469 --> 02:59.679
I JUST NEED SOME WATER.

02:59.929 --> 03:01.556
AH, I'M SO HOT.

03:01.806 --> 03:02.974
CRACK INTO A COUPLE
OF COCONUTS.

03:03.308 --> 03:04.851
[SIGHS] I CAN DO IT, I JUST...

03:05.226 --> 03:07.103
I JUST NEED TO GET SOME WATER.

03:09.606 --> 03:10.982
[GULPING]

03:11.065 --> 03:13.109
[GASPS] HAPPY?

03:13.192 --> 03:14.986
WHERE ARE YOU, BOY?

03:15.069 --> 03:17.238
OH, OFFICIAL
BUSINESS [CHUCKLES].

03:17.488 --> 03:19.782
WHAT?

03:20.033 --> 03:22.827
HAPPY, YOU DON'T USUALLY GO OUT
THIS LATE FOR A BATHROOM BREAK.

03:23.077 --> 03:25.288
[CLOCK TICKING...]

03:34.672 --> 03:38.384
[TICKING CONTINUES...]

03:38.635 --> 03:41.429
[CRICKET CHIRPS]

03:41.679 --> 03:43.973
[TICKING...]

03:47.101 --> 03:47.769
Sandman: AY-YEE!

03:50.188 --> 03:52.023
[AUDIBLE GASP]

03:52.315 --> 03:52.815
[TICKING CONTINUES...]

03:59.238 --> 04:01.866
[YAWNS... SNORING]

04:06.537 --> 04:07.538
[SNORTS AWAKE]

04:07.789 --> 04:09.374
BREAKFAST?

04:09.624 --> 04:10.917
THANK YOU, HAPPY.

04:11.167 --> 04:15.088
SO... HOW DID YOU SLEEP?

04:15.338 --> 04:17.173
[INNOCENT GROWL]

04:17.423 --> 04:19.591
REALLY?

04:19.841 --> 04:21.052
SLEPT LIKE A ROCK, HUH?

04:21.135 --> 04:23.346
[INNOCENT BARK]

04:23.596 --> 04:25.098
OH, I SLEPT JUST FINE.

04:25.390 --> 04:27.517
UNTIL I WOKE UP PARCHED

04:27.767 --> 04:29.602
{\an6}AND I CAME DOWN
TO THE KITCHEN
FOR A GLASS OF WATER

04:29.852 --> 04:30.478
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE NIGHT.

04:32.814 --> 04:34.857
[GRUMBLING]

04:35.108 --> 04:37.068
{\an3}INTERESTING, YES,
I THOUGHT SO.

04:37.151 --> 04:38.778
SO WHAT ARE YOU
DOING TONIGHT?

04:39.028 --> 04:40.363
ANY PLANS?

04:42.740 --> 04:46.077
[GROWL-LIKE:
"OH, NOT MUCH"]

04:46.160 --> 04:48.955
GREAT, WHAT DO YOU SAY WE DO
"NOT MUCH" TOGETHER, HM?

04:51.874 --> 04:53.543
[BARKS]

04:53.793 --> 04:55.712
Bessie: [SIGHS] AN EVENING IN.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.131
THIS IS DELIGHTFUL, AYE, HAPPY?

04:58.423 --> 04:59.590
[HAPPY BARKS]

04:59.841 --> 05:01.050
YOUR MOVE.

05:05.013 --> 05:06.723
[NERVOUS BARK]

05:06.973 --> 05:07.807
SUCH FUN WE'RE HAVING,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

05:14.147 --> 05:15.606
{\an3}[YAWNING]

05:20.319 --> 05:21.070
[YAWNS]

05:27.952 --> 05:27.994
[YAWNS]

05:30.329 --> 05:33.750
[STRUGGLING GROAN]

05:34.000 --> 05:35.376
[YAWNS DRAMATICALLY]

05:38.755 --> 05:41.090
[BIG YAWN]

05:41.174 --> 05:43.009
[BIGGER YAWN]

05:43.259 --> 05:45.261
[NOISY YAWN]

05:45.344 --> 05:46.846
[YAWNING CONTINUES]

05:53.478 --> 05:56.064
[YAWNING]: BOY,
AM I WIDE AWAKE.

05:56.355 --> 05:58.107
I HAVE AN IDEA.

05:58.399 --> 06:01.069
WHY DON'T WE WATCH
A NICE LOUD ACTION MOVIE?

06:01.360 --> 06:02.528
WHO WANTS TO SEE SOME
CARS GETTING BLOWN UP?

06:08.618 --> 06:10.203
[GUNFIRE...]

06:10.453 --> 06:12.538
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

06:12.789 --> 06:15.291
TV Announcer: [SOOTHING VOICE]:
Tired of being tired?

06:15.541 --> 06:17.418
[SLEEPY MOAN]

06:17.668 --> 06:20.421
...Why not cuddle on a cloud?

06:20.671 --> 06:23.132
Our big, soft,
fluffy, mattresses

06:23.216 --> 06:26.260
guarantee a blissful
night's sleep.

06:26.344 --> 06:27.970
[YAWNING]

06:37.480 --> 06:40.066
{\an5}Bessie: MUST...

06:37.480 --> 06:40.066
[MAN SNORES ON TV...]

06:40.399 --> 06:43.444
STAY...

06:43.694 --> 06:45.279
...AWAKE.

06:45.363 --> 06:48.533
[MUSIC PLAYS AT SLOW SPEED]

06:48.783 --> 06:50.660
[MUSIC SLOWS DOWN...]

06:50.910 --> 06:51.536
[CAR STARTING]

06:54.580 --> 06:56.874
Man: [ON RADIO]
♪ CAN I COME 'ROUND, BABY?

06:57.125 --> 06:59.794
♪ I WANNA COME 'ROUND... ♪

07:00.044 --> 07:01.254
[TIRES SQUEAL]

07:01.629 --> 07:03.714
♪ CAN I COME 'ROUND, BABY? ♪

07:03.965 --> 07:06.926
{\an5}♪ OH, WILL YOU BE DOWN... ♪

07:03.965 --> 07:06.926
[ENGINE REVS...]

07:07.260 --> 07:08.511
[ENGINE REVS]

07:08.594 --> 07:09.345
AH!

07:13.558 --> 07:14.559
WHOA!

07:16.435 --> 07:18.646
♪ ...DOWN WITH IT, BABY ♪

07:18.896 --> 07:20.356
♪ OH, WILL YOU BE DOWN... ♪

07:28.281 --> 07:30.658
[BESSIE SCREAMS]

07:30.908 --> 07:32.368
WHOA!

07:32.451 --> 07:35.913
[SCREAMING]

07:36.164 --> 07:38.166
OH!

07:38.416 --> 07:40.710
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.628
♪ THIS FEELING,
WHAT I'M FEELING... ♪

07:42.879 --> 07:44.380
[BARKS]: HUH?

07:44.463 --> 07:46.007
♪ WELL, I GUESS YOU KNOW ♪

07:46.257 --> 07:48.384
♪ BEEN ASKING AROUND A LOT ♪

07:48.634 --> 07:51.345
WHOA, OHH...

07:51.596 --> 07:51.637
AHH!

07:55.391 --> 07:55.933
{\an5}[SCREAMING]

07:55.391 --> 07:55.933
[BIRDS TWITTER]

07:57.894 --> 07:59.228
AHH! OHH!

07:59.312 --> 08:01.230
[SQUIRREL CHATTERING]

08:04.901 --> 08:05.651
[CHATTERING]

08:09.780 --> 08:11.657
[TIRES SQUEAL]

08:11.908 --> 08:13.034
[GASPS]

08:13.284 --> 08:14.619
{\an1}...HAPPY?

08:14.869 --> 08:16.329
[STAMMERING]:
WHA... WHAT?

08:16.579 --> 08:17.747
YOU'RE DRESSED
ALL IN BLACK?

08:17.997 --> 08:19.207
WHAT IN THE WORLD?

08:19.457 --> 08:20.750
WHAT COULD YOU BE...

08:21.000 --> 08:22.585
{\an1}[GASPS]
CAT BURGLARING?

08:22.835 --> 08:23.961
BUT YOU HATE CATS.

08:27.590 --> 08:28.883
UGH.

08:29.133 --> 08:30.134
[GROWLS]

08:39.101 --> 08:41.145
[GROWLING]

08:47.985 --> 08:49.528
[HOWLING]

08:49.779 --> 08:52.240
[GASPS] A SPECIAL HANDSHAKE?

08:52.490 --> 08:55.368
[GASPS] ARMED ROBBERY.

08:55.660 --> 08:57.954
OH, NO, I WON'T LET YOU
GO DOWN THIS ROAD, BOY.

08:58.204 --> 08:59.330
[LOUD CLANK]

08:59.413 --> 09:00.289
[GROWLS]: HUH?

09:03.584 --> 09:04.710
[JOYFUL YELP]

09:04.961 --> 09:06.796
[PANTING]

09:07.046 --> 09:09.090
HAPPY, I CAN'T
LET YOU [GASPS]...

09:09.340 --> 09:13.302
[TANGO MUSIC PLAYS]

09:13.386 --> 09:15.429
[BARKS]

09:13.386 --> 09:15.429
SORRY.

09:20.393 --> 09:23.437
[DOGS BARKING]

09:23.521 --> 09:26.899
[APPLAUSE... DOGS BARKING]

09:27.149 --> 09:28.526
HAPPY?

09:30.528 --> 09:33.239
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYS]

09:40.746 --> 09:42.373
SHIRLEY TEMPLE, PLEASE.

09:42.623 --> 09:44.000
{\an1}HEAVY ON THE GRENADINE
AND SIX CHERRIES.

09:53.592 --> 09:54.885
[MUSIC ENDS]

09:55.136 --> 09:56.971
[APPLAUSE AND BARKING]

09:59.015 --> 10:02.351
HAPPY, THAT WAS AMAZING!

10:02.435 --> 10:02.727
[BARKS]: HUH?

10:04.979 --> 10:05.938
[EMBARRASSED MOAN]

10:08.399 --> 10:09.317
[ALL GROWLING]

10:09.608 --> 10:11.360
[IRRITATED BARK]

10:11.652 --> 10:14.071
SORRY... BUT WHY DIDN'T
YOU JUST TELL ME, BOY?

10:14.322 --> 10:16.157
{\an5}[GRUMBLES]

10:14.322 --> 10:16.157
WOULDN'T
UNDERSTAND?

10:16.490 --> 10:18.075
WELL, IT'S
PERFECTLY ACCEPTABLE

10:18.326 --> 10:19.869
FOR BOY DOGS
TO DANCE, HAPPY.

10:20.119 --> 10:22.496
AND YOU'RE A NATURAL-
I'M SO PROUD.

10:22.580 --> 10:25.833
[TANGO MUSIC PLAYS]

10:27.793 --> 10:30.880
REALLY, YOU WOULDN'T
BE EMBARRASSED?

10:31.130 --> 10:32.131
{\an3}WELL, I DON'T REALLY KNOW
HOW TO DANCE, BUT, YES.

10:52.777 --> 10:55.196
[APPLAUSE... DOGS HOWLING]

10:55.446 --> 10:58.074
WELL, HAPS,
ENJOY THE REST OF THE NIGHT.

10:58.324 --> 11:00.076
{\an5}BUT YOU KNOW WHAT,
DOGS REALLY SHOULDN'T
BE DRIVING

11:00.326 --> 11:03.371
SO FROM NOW ON... [YAWNS]

11:03.621 --> 11:05.247
JUST WATCH THE SPEED LIMIT.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.832
[YAWNING]

11:09.502 --> 11:11.420
[BESSIE SNORES]

11:09.502 --> 11:11.420
{\an3}[KISS]

11:11.504 --> 11:12.797
BYE, HAPPY,
SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.

11:20.346 --> 11:21.389
[WHISTLES]

11:25.518 --> 11:28.270
[UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS...]

11:28.521 --> 11:29.605
[BELLS DING]

11:33.025 --> 11:34.610
[JOYFUL BARK]

11:36.070 --> 11:39.073
[♪...]

11:47.039 --> 11:48.582
Millie: AND ALSO,
SOMETIMES WHEN WE PLAY

11:48.874 --> 11:49.834
{\an1}CHESTER TURTLETON
AND ME ESKIMO KISS.

11:53.546 --> 11:57.174
AND ALSO SOMETIMES NOT.

11:57.425 --> 11:59.635
{\an3}IF I GIVE YOU
THE PET LOVER'S BADGE

11:59.718 --> 12:02.221
{\an3}DO YOU PROMISE NEVER TO EXPOSE
US TO YOUR REPTILE AGAIN?

12:05.933 --> 12:08.269
BRAVO, BRAVO.

12:08.519 --> 12:11.188
AND NOW, LADY AND BEES

12:11.439 --> 12:14.483
{\an5}AS LONG AS
WE ARE INDISCRIMINATELY
GIVING OUT BADGES

12:14.567 --> 12:16.277
I WOULD LIKE
TO MAKE AN ANNOUNCEMENT.

12:16.527 --> 12:19.822
I, THE GREAT BEE-DINI...

12:20.072 --> 12:22.032
[LAUGHING]

12:22.283 --> 12:24.493
IN AN ATTEMPT TO EARN
THE ELUSIVE TA-DA BADGE

12:24.743 --> 12:27.997
WILL HOST A MAGIC SHOW
AT THE HIVE.

12:28.247 --> 12:29.415
WATCH IT.

12:29.665 --> 12:30.833
OOPS, SORRY, P.

12:31.083 --> 12:32.251
STILL WORKING ON MY MOVES.

12:32.501 --> 12:34.044
JUST A PREVIEW

12:34.295 --> 12:36.380
OF SOME OF THE SHAZAMMY STUFF

12:36.630 --> 12:39.717
YOU CAN EXPECT
FROM THE GREAT BEE-DINI.

12:39.967 --> 12:41.427
All: OHH...

12:41.677 --> 12:42.803
{\an1}...AHH.

12:43.053 --> 12:45.055
ANYWAY, COME TO MY SHOW

12:45.306 --> 12:47.892
AND YOU WILL SEE ME SAW MY
LOVELY ASSISTANT IN HALF.

12:49.643 --> 12:51.520
[BARKS]

12:51.604 --> 12:53.439
{\an1}IT'S NOT ANIMAL CRUELTY,
IT'S JUST MAGIC.

12:53.689 --> 12:55.483
ALL RIGHT, BESSIE,
JUST REMEMBER-

12:55.816 --> 12:58.611
THE TA-DA BADGE IS AWARDED
BASED ON AUDIENCE RESPONSE.

12:58.903 --> 13:00.404
RIGHT YOU ARE, MRS. GIBBONS.

13:00.654 --> 13:02.198
COME ONE, COME ALL.

13:02.448 --> 13:04.617
BRING FRIENDS, PETS, LOVED ONES

13:04.909 --> 13:07.286
EX-NEIGHBORS, OLD TEACHERS,
LONELY PEOPLE, HOBOS...

13:07.536 --> 13:09.705
AND ANYONE WHO'S
JUST HANGIN' AROUND.

13:11.707 --> 13:14.293
[WIND HOWLING]

13:14.543 --> 13:16.712
...ALL RIGHT GUYS, WE ARE
DOING A DRESS REHEARSAL.

13:16.795 --> 13:19.924
THAT MEANS WE ARE
REHEARSING IN DRESS.

13:20.174 --> 13:22.301
AND NOW,
IN A DRAMATIC TURN OF EVENTS

13:22.551 --> 13:24.094
HAPPY WILL BE MY RABBIT.

13:24.345 --> 13:25.804
[GROWLS]

13:26.055 --> 13:27.181
UGH.

13:27.431 --> 13:29.183
OH, MY APOLOGIES.

13:29.433 --> 13:31.310
AND THE ROLE
OF THE LOVELY ASSISTANT

13:31.560 --> 13:34.688
WILL NOW BE PLAYED
BY NONE OTHER THAN BEN.

13:34.772 --> 13:36.023
THIS IS STUPID.

13:36.273 --> 13:38.692
THIS IS A GIRL'S JOB.

13:39.026 --> 13:42.154
{\an5}MAY I REMIND YOU THAT
THE TERM "LOVELY ASSISTANT"
IS NOT <i> GENDER</i> SPECIFIC.

13:42.404 --> 13:44.198
THEN WHY DO I HAVE
TO WEAR TIGHTS?

13:44.448 --> 13:46.367
{\an3}TRADITION.

13:46.617 --> 13:48.744
{\an1}BESIDES, SOMEONE HAD
TO PLAY THE RABBIT

13:48.827 --> 13:50.579
AND HAPPY GRACIOUSLY
VOLUNTEERED.

13:50.871 --> 13:54.583
...Volunteered... [ECHO]

13:54.667 --> 13:56.752
Bessie: [LAUGHS]
AH, THAT'S SO FUNNY.

13:56.835 --> 13:58.128
LOOK IT, YOU'RE A CLOWN.

13:58.379 --> 14:01.048
[DISCO MUSIC PLAYS]

14:01.131 --> 14:02.091
{\an1}[CRASH]

14:04.718 --> 14:05.010
[BARKS]

14:07.846 --> 14:10.224
[GROWLS]

14:10.474 --> 14:12.476
[GRUMBLES]

14:12.726 --> 14:15.854
{\an1}OK... SEANCES,
STRAITJACKETS...

14:16.105 --> 14:17.690
FREEZING YOURSELF
IN A BLOCK OF ICE.

14:17.982 --> 14:20.109
THAT'S MAGIC?

14:20.192 --> 14:21.402
RABBITS!

14:21.652 --> 14:22.736
[GRUNTS]

14:22.820 --> 14:23.779
HERE WE GO.

14:24.029 --> 14:25.489
ALACAZAM...

14:25.739 --> 14:26.949
ALACAZAP...

14:27.199 --> 14:29.702
SEND HAPPY THE BUNNY

14:29.952 --> 14:30.035
INTO MY HAT.

14:32.746 --> 14:33.497
TA-DA.

14:37.876 --> 14:39.545
OK, ONE MORE TIME.

14:39.795 --> 14:40.754
HERE WE GO,
HERE WE GO.

14:41.046 --> 14:42.590
ALACAZAM, ALACAZAT...

14:42.840 --> 14:44.800
SEND HAPPY THE BUNNY

14:44.883 --> 14:46.802
INTO MY HAT.

14:46.885 --> 14:47.761
RAT-A-TAT-TAT.

14:48.012 --> 14:48.053
{\an1}...TA-DA.

14:52.057 --> 14:53.309
[GASPING]

14:53.559 --> 14:54.643
UH, UH, IT WORKED.

14:54.935 --> 14:56.186
BEN, IT WORKED.

14:56.437 --> 14:58.522
UM, NO, IT DIDN'T.

14:58.772 --> 15:00.899
UM, DID YOU SEE HAPPY
SITTING HERE- DIDN'T THINK SO.

15:01.150 --> 15:03.402
{\an3}CAN YOU SAY CONCLUSIVE
EVIDENCE, BEN?

15:03.652 --> 15:05.696
CAN YOU SAY, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT?

15:05.779 --> 15:07.781
SILENCE.

15:07.865 --> 15:09.617
AND NOW FOR MY NEXT
FEAT OF WONDERMENT

15:09.950 --> 15:13.245
I, THE AMAZING BEE-DINI,
WILL REVERSE THE SPELL.

15:14.913 --> 15:16.165
[CLEARS THROAT]

15:16.415 --> 15:18.083
ALACAZAM, ALACAZAC.

15:18.334 --> 15:22.212
BRING HAPPY THE BUNNY
RIGHT BACK.

15:22.463 --> 15:24.465
RIGHT BACK.

15:24.715 --> 15:25.674
THIS TIME I'M NOT
PLAYING AROUND.

15:25.966 --> 15:28.510
AND... RIGHT BACK.

15:28.761 --> 15:32.640
NOW, NOW, NOW.

15:32.931 --> 15:37.186
NOW, NOW, NOW.

15:37.436 --> 15:38.687
UGH, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON.

15:38.771 --> 15:40.022
IT WORKED A MINUTE AGO.

15:40.272 --> 15:42.524
[RELIEVED SIGH]

15:42.775 --> 15:44.276
HUH?

15:44.526 --> 15:44.610
[BARKS]

15:49.907 --> 15:50.699
[BARKING]

16:02.294 --> 16:04.046
[HAPPY YELPS]

16:04.296 --> 16:05.881
[MUFFLED AND ECHOING]:
HAPPY, HAPPY...

16:05.964 --> 16:07.716
PLEASE ANSWER ME, BOY.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.760
THE SHOW IS
GONNA START SOON.

16:09.843 --> 16:11.637
LISTEN TO ME ALREADY.

16:11.887 --> 16:12.805
{\an1}HAPPY...

16:11.887 --> 16:12.805
BEN, PLEASE.

16:13.180 --> 16:16.475
ALACAZAM, ALACAZAC.

16:16.725 --> 16:19.603
PLEASE, PLEASE,<i> PLEASE,</i>
BRING HAPPY RIGHT BACK.

16:19.853 --> 16:21.730
Portia: HAH, NO HEAD.

16:21.814 --> 16:23.774
THAT'S A GOOD LOOK FOR YOU.

16:24.024 --> 16:26.860
{\an4}HEH, HOW 'BOUT
YOU PULL A NEW WARDROBE
OUT OF THAT HAT?

16:26.944 --> 16:29.905
{\an5}YEAH, WHY DON'T YOU
MAKE THAT ONE OF
YOUR THREE WISHES?

16:29.988 --> 16:31.156
[ALL LAUGHING]

16:31.407 --> 16:33.117
[BESSIE GRUNTS]

16:33.367 --> 16:34.493
THIS IS NOT
A GENIE BOTTLE, PORTIA.

16:34.743 --> 16:35.869
IT IS A MAGIC HAT

16:36.203 --> 16:37.788
AND HAPPY IS STUCK INSIDE OF IT.

16:38.038 --> 16:39.790
[SNICKERING]

16:39.873 --> 16:41.917
I KEEPING TRYING
TO TELL HER...

16:42.000 --> 16:43.127
BEN, YOUR JOB IS TO STAND
THERE AND BE LOVELY.

16:46.004 --> 16:48.215
UM, IF YOU'RE SO RAD AT MAGIC

16:48.465 --> 16:50.884
MAKE <i> ME</i> DISAPPEAR
AND I'LL GO LOOK FOR HIM.

16:51.135 --> 16:53.137
[LAUGHING]

16:53.387 --> 16:55.264
[GASPS] YOU WOULD
DO THAT FOR ME?

16:55.514 --> 16:58.684
SURE, THAT'S WHAT
BEES ARE FOR, RIGHT?

16:58.934 --> 16:59.935
OK, OK.

17:00.227 --> 17:02.813
ALACAZAM, ALACAZAT.

17:02.896 --> 17:04.522
FORCES OF MAGIC...

17:04.772 --> 17:08.359
SEND PORTIA INTO MY HAT.

17:08.609 --> 17:09.653
[RUMBLING]

17:09.903 --> 17:10.945
[GASPING]

17:11.029 --> 17:11.195
[GASPS]

17:14.907 --> 17:18.619
HEY, TURN THE LIGHTS ON.

17:18.871 --> 17:20.455
SERIOUSLY.

17:20.705 --> 17:23.125
[ECHOING]:
IS HAPPY IN THERE?

17:23.375 --> 17:26.086
CAN YOU TRY
CALLING HIM?

17:26.336 --> 17:27.755
WHERE AM I?

17:28.005 --> 17:29.798
WHAT'S GOING ON?

17:29.882 --> 17:32.968
Bessie: AS DISCUSSED,
YOU ARE IN MY HAT!

17:33.260 --> 17:34.887
GET ME OUT OF HERE.

17:35.220 --> 17:38.223
I REPEAT, PORTIA,
DO YOU SEE MY RABBIT-DOG?

17:38.474 --> 17:40.809
YOUR DUMB DOG ISN'T DOWN HERE.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.811
NOW MAGIC ME
OUT OF HERE, PRONTO!

17:43.103 --> 17:44.646
FOR THE LAST TIME....

17:44.897 --> 17:45.939
{\an1}Bessie:
TRY CALLING HIM.

17:46.023 --> 17:48.776
HAPPY?

17:49.026 --> 17:51.195
HERE, HAPPY.

17:51.445 --> 17:53.322
THAT WAS GREAT.

17:53.572 --> 17:55.783
LET'S TRY IT LOUDER
THIS TIME... AND NICER.

17:56.033 --> 17:57.868
OR TELL HIM
THAT YOU HAVE A BISCUIT.

17:57.951 --> 17:59.745
{\an3}...I DON'T LIKE
TO RESORT TO THAT

17:59.995 --> 18:01.497
{\an3}BUT HE FALLS
FOR IT EVERY TIME.

18:01.747 --> 18:02.998
Portia: HAPPY?

18:03.081 --> 18:05.292
[SCREAMS]: HELP!

18:05.542 --> 18:07.127
[CRASH]

18:07.377 --> 18:08.253
{\an5}[ALL
GASPING]

18:07.377 --> 18:08.253
[DOOR OPENS]

18:08.587 --> 18:09.963
BESSIE...

18:10.047 --> 18:13.759
...YOUR AUDIENCE IS HERE.

18:14.009 --> 18:15.511
All: AHH...

18:15.761 --> 18:18.680
[WHISPERS]: PORTIA, PORTIA?

18:18.931 --> 18:20.557
Mary Frances: OH, HI, BEES.

18:20.808 --> 18:22.309
HAS ANYONE SEEN
MON PETIT PORTIA?

18:22.559 --> 18:23.852
{\an3}NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO-NO-NO...

18:25.813 --> 18:28.023
UH, NO WORRIES, MRS. GIBBONS.

18:28.106 --> 18:31.568
UH, PORTIA JUST RAN OUT TO PICK
UP A NEW PAIR OF FISHNETS.

18:31.819 --> 18:33.904
FOR BEN, YOU KNOW...

18:33.987 --> 18:35.531
'CAUSE HE GOT A RUN IN HIS
SO HE'S A... PERFECTIONIST.

18:44.790 --> 18:47.876
[ALL BARKING]

18:48.126 --> 18:48.502
[HAPPY YELPS]

18:50.379 --> 18:51.588
[YELPS... GROWLS]

18:54.132 --> 18:56.468
[YELPS... GROANS]

18:56.718 --> 18:58.303
[DOGS CHOMPING...]

18:58.554 --> 18:59.888
[HAPPY GROANS]

19:00.138 --> 19:01.139
[SIGHS]

19:01.390 --> 19:02.933
{\an1}[GROANING]

19:04.935 --> 19:07.646
[DISTANT HORN HONKING]

19:07.896 --> 19:10.315
[DISTANT CAR ALARM BLARES...]

19:12.276 --> 19:15.362
[DOGS LAUGHING]

19:15.612 --> 19:16.154
[EMBARRASSED LAUGH]

19:19.157 --> 19:20.200
[ALL LAUGHING]

19:20.450 --> 19:20.742
[CHOMPING]

19:25.122 --> 19:26.832
OH, WHAT'S THIS?

19:27.165 --> 19:30.377
IN MY EAR... A QUARTER.

19:30.627 --> 19:33.589
[ALL SIGH]

19:33.839 --> 19:35.257
[AUDIENCE MURMURING]

19:35.507 --> 19:37.175
WAIT, PLEASE, DON'T LEAVE.

19:37.426 --> 19:39.595
UM, FOR MY NEXT FEAT

19:39.845 --> 19:42.347
SOME GOOD OLD-FASHIONED
PRESTIDIGITATION

19:42.598 --> 19:45.934
OR AS IT'S SOMETIMES KNOWN TO
MERE MORTALS, SLEIGHT OF HAND.

19:46.018 --> 19:47.728
AND HERE WE GO... OH, BOY.

19:47.978 --> 19:49.021
[AUDIENCE JEERS]

19:49.271 --> 19:50.814
ROUGH.

19:51.064 --> 19:52.482
Ben: COVER FOR ME.

19:52.733 --> 19:55.485
[DOGS SNORING...]

20:00.198 --> 20:01.992
[STRETCHING GROAN]

20:02.242 --> 20:03.535
[PAINFUL YELP]

20:03.785 --> 20:07.122
[STRETCHING GROWL]

20:07.205 --> 20:09.124
[GROANS]

20:09.207 --> 20:10.250
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

20:10.500 --> 20:11.627
[YELPS]: HUH?

20:11.877 --> 20:12.920
LET'S GO, HAPPY.

20:13.170 --> 20:13.962
[GROWLS]

20:14.212 --> 20:16.214
[SIGHS]

20:16.465 --> 20:19.259
Bessie: UM, AND NOW,
FOR ONE OF MY BEST TRICKS...

20:19.509 --> 20:22.471
I WILL SAW MY LOVELY
ASSISTANT IN HALF.

20:22.721 --> 20:25.849
{\an3}OH, BESSIE?

20:22.721 --> 20:25.849
{\an1}PENNY?

20:26.183 --> 20:28.477
Ben: I DON'T CARE ABOUT
YOUR STUPID HERNIATED DISC.

20:28.727 --> 20:30.812
{\an1}YOU'RE GOING INTO THAT HAT
SO SHE CAN PULL YOU OUT.

20:31.063 --> 20:31.355
{\an3}[GRUMBLES]

20:36.818 --> 20:37.319
{\an3}[SCREAMS]

20:36.818 --> 20:37.319
AHH!

20:40.072 --> 20:40.280
WHOA...

20:42.032 --> 20:44.159
AH, OOH.

20:44.242 --> 20:45.953
OK, EVERYBODY, JOKE BREAK.

20:46.244 --> 20:48.413
UM, WHO'S READY FOR SOME
KILLER KNOCK-KNOCKS?

20:48.664 --> 20:51.166
[AUDIENCE GROANING]

20:51.250 --> 20:52.501
UM, KNOCK-KNOCK,
WHO'S THERE?

20:52.751 --> 20:54.378
I FORGET THE OTHER PART.

20:54.461 --> 20:55.712
UM...

20:55.963 --> 20:59.174
ALACA...ALACAZAM.

20:59.257 --> 21:02.594
ALACA... OH, WAIT A MINUTE,
WAIT, JUST A SECOND.

21:02.844 --> 21:03.595
[GRUMBLES]

21:05.222 --> 21:06.264
HEY.

21:06.515 --> 21:09.476
[BARKING THE SPELL]

21:09.726 --> 21:11.103
{\an3}WHOA.

21:11.353 --> 21:14.648
{\an5}[MUFFLED BARKING]

21:11.353 --> 21:14.648
WHAT THE...

21:14.982 --> 21:17.192
[HAPPY BARKING]

21:17.275 --> 21:20.112
Portia: SHUT THE DOOR...
FREEZING!

21:20.404 --> 21:21.738
Audience: OHH...

21:21.989 --> 21:23.323
[APPLAUSE... METER DINGS]

21:23.573 --> 21:24.866
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

21:25.117 --> 21:27.202
WITHOUT FURTHER ADO.

21:27.285 --> 21:30.205
I WILL MAKE A RABBIT-DOG APPEAR
BEFORE YOUR VERY EYES.

21:30.455 --> 21:32.124
ALACAZAM...

21:30.455 --> 21:32.124
ALACAZAM...

21:32.457 --> 21:34.418
{\an5}ALACAZAC...

21:32.457 --> 21:34.418
ALACAZAC,
MAGIC HAT.

21:34.751 --> 21:36.712
{\an4}PLEASE BRING MY
RABBIT-DOG...

21:34.751 --> 21:36.712
PLEASE GIVE HAPPY

21:37.045 --> 21:37.129
{\an5}RIGHT BACK.

21:37.045 --> 21:37.129
AND ALL THE OTHER
BEASTS RIGHT BACK.

21:38.588 --> 21:40.590
[RUMBLING AND SCREAMING]

21:42.384 --> 21:43.176
[SCREAMING]

21:46.722 --> 21:49.057
[CHEERING]

21:49.141 --> 21:51.309
[METER BELL DINGS]

21:51.560 --> 21:52.936
[EXPLOSION]

21:53.186 --> 21:55.605
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

21:55.856 --> 21:58.400
[GASPS] ♪ TA-DA,
TA-DA, TA-DA ♪

